_Things that are inconsistent_

euca-describe-services shows everything being ENABLED, however there are the following inconsistencies:
* Heartbeat shows node not being enabled
{code}
name=node                 enabled=false      local=true       initialized=true
{code}
* Describe-components shows the following components in PRIMORDIAL state
{code}
COMPONENT	eucalyptus     	{}             	{}                       	{}	PRIMORDIAL	{}
COMPONENT	cluster        	{}             	{}                       	{}	PRIMORDIAL	{}
COMPONENT	bootstrap      	{}             	{}                       	{}	PRIMORDIAL	{}
{code}
* Describe-components doesn't include any nodes

*Steps*

* Set up a Eucalyptus 3.4 cloud
* Ensure all components are registered
* Compare status of the outputs from the following commands:
** curl http://CLCIPADDRESS:8773/services/Heartbeat
** euca-describe-components
** euca-describe-services

*Pertinent Data*

Although it looks like euca-describe-services is ground truth, it does confuse cloud administrators when those services are not consistent; especially when determining if the cloud is healthy or not.  Also, depending upon components registered, and the topology of the cloud, the inconsistency between all three will be different. 

*Workarounds*

N/A

